{"errorLabel":null,"results":[{"type":"APPEAL","typeLabel":"Appeal","date":"27/03/2026","uniqueSolrKey":"APL_20260327_R1967_2025-2_018063926","url":"https://euipo.europa.eu/eSearchCLW/#key/trademark/APL_20260327_R1967_2025-2_018063926","languagesOriginal":[{"code":"es","label":"Spanish","pdfUrl":"https://euipo.europa.eu/copla/trademark/data/018063926/download/CLW/APL/2026/ES/20260327_R1967_2025-2.pdf?app=caselaw&casenum=R1967/2025-2&trTypeDoc=NA"}],"languagesHumanTranslated":[],"languagesMachineTranslated":[{"code":"en","label":"English (en)","pdfUrl":"https://euipo.europa.eu/copla/trademark/data/018063926/download/CLW/APL/2026/EN/20260327_R1967_2025-2.pdf?app=caselaw&casenum=R1967/2025-2&trTypeDoc=eTranslation&sourceLang=es","serviceProvider":"eTranslation"},{"code":"fr","label":"français (fr)","pdfUrl":"https://euipo.europa.eu/copla/trademark/data/018063926/download/CLW/APL/2026/FR/20260327_R1967_2025-2.pdf?app=caselaw&casenum=R1967/2025-2&trTypeDoc=eTranslation&sourceLang=es","serviceProvider":"eTranslation"},{"code":"it","label":"italiano (it)","pdfUrl":"https://euipo.europa.eu/copla/trademark/data/018063926/download/CLW/APL/2026/IT/20260327_R1967_2025-2.pdf?app=caselaw&casenum=R1967/2025-2&trTypeDoc=eTranslation&sourceLang=es","serviceProvider":"eTranslation"}],"quotation":"(27/03/2026, R 1967/2025‑2, WIOHAIR BEAUTIFUL HAIR (fig.))","documentKind":"Decision","caseNumber":"R1967/2025-2","ipRight":"EUTM","outcome":"Decision confirmed","appealed":"No","entityNumber":"018063926","entityStatus":"Registration cancellation pending","norms":["Article 59(1)(b) EUTMR"],"relatedCases":[{"id":"CCL_20250903_000067265_018063926","label":"Cancellation decision 000067265","url":"https://euipo.europa.eu/eSearchCLW/#key/trademark/CCL_20250903_000067265_018063926"}],"entityImage":"/copla/image/CJ4JX4FZVCC523YA2TMALSKFLGCWJTJRC3GXC3527YOL7FRIQNPZS4SSKKGKJ2RWXN45ZSM3ATRNA","entityName":"WIOHAIR BEAUTIFUL HAIR","entityType":"Figurative","nickName":"WIOHAIR BEAUTIFUL HAIR (fig.)","keywords":["Bad faith (Yes)","Bad faith"],"summary":"The Board agrees with the Cancellation Division in finding that the EUTM proprietor acted in bad faith at the time of filing the contested EUTM application.\n\nThe objective facts established in the present case, assessed globally, are as follows: (i) the name WIOHAIR was conceived within the framework of the contractual relationship between the parties and its origin is directly linked to the cancellation applicant; (ii) at the time of filing the application, the EUTM proprietor was fully aware of the existence of the sign and of its link with the cancellation applicant; (iii) the Agreement was fully in force on the filing date; (iv) the Agreement did not contain any express and unconditional authorisation allowing the EUTM proprietor to proceed with the registration of the mark unilaterally, but rather contemplated registration as a future decision to be taken in the context of the development of the project; (v) the EUTM proprietor filed the application unilaterally, without prior communication to or consent from the cancellation applicant; and (vi) the EUTM proprietor has not put forward any plausible justification for the commercial rationale underlying its conduct.\n\nAll these elements, taken together, are incompatible with honest commercial practices and reveal a dishonest intention on the part of the EUTM proprietor, consisting in the unilateral appropriation of the sign which was the subject of the contractual relationship and of which the cancellation applicant was the creator and legitimate owner, thereby effectively preventing the latter from continuing to use the sign for its products.","earlierName":"(Trade mark without text)","entityResult":"Trade mark declared invalid","deemedDeliveredToAppellantDate":"04/04/2026","deemedDeliveredToDefendantDate":"04/04/2026"},{"type":"CANCELLATION","typeLabel":"Cancellation decision","date":"27/03/2026","uniqueSolrKey":"CCL_20260327_000072469_019121654","url":"http